repnme.cdata!:
Bosnia and Herzegovina - Enterprise and
            Banking Privatization Adjustment Credit Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The outcome of the Enterprise &
            Banking Privatization Adjustment Credit Project for Bosnia
            and Herzegovina was satisfactory, the sustainability was
            likely, the institutional development impact was
            substantial, and the Bank and borrower performance were both
            satisfactory. The lessons learned indicate that a complex
            adjustment project in terms of sector coverage and country
            conditions can be successful despite a marginal quality at
            entry assessment if the government commitment remains high
            and is demonstrated through key policy actions. Supervision
            of the project is flexible in terms of responsiveness to the
            borrower's changing situation and intensive in terms of
            monitoring and adherence to priority conditions. For initial
            adjustment credits in private sector development, it is best
            to set conditions for the first tranche release that do not
            involve major actions that are likely to be controversial
            delaying the start of the project. Establish a viable
            implementation timeline for privatization adjustment
            operations. Recognize the advantages of strategic
            privatization and need for expert privatization assistance
            early in the project preparation.

repnme.cdata!:
Bosnia and Herzegovina - Enterprise and
            Bank Privatization Adjustment Credit Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The Enterprise and Bank Privatization
            Adjustment Credit Project for Bosnia and Herzegovina aims to
            fund privatization of enterprises and banks and
            implementation of policy reforms at the entity level.
            Specifically, the project will help 1) develop the design,
            legal framework and regulations, and the institutional
            strengthening and implementing of the program to privatize
            solvent publicly-owned commercial banks and liquidate
            insolvent ones; 2) reform the financial sector to improve
            bank supervision, strengthen banking laws, establish deposit
            insurance systems, and limit public intervention in credit
            markets; and 3) complete the institutional and legal
            framework for enterprise privatization, including rapid
            initiation of small enterprise privatization, and
            preparation for privatization of larger enterprises, holding
            companies, and utilities. In addition, the Credit provides
            support for reforming the legal and institutional framework
            needed for private sector development. The Credit will be
            disbursed in two tranches for budgetary and balance of
            payments support to the two entities of Bosnia and
            Herzegovina. The release of tranches will be linked to
            policy conditionality as agreed.
